Label: SpecimenType
Description: Type of biological material comprising the Specimen

Label: SamplingAge
Description: The calculated age of the sample, measurement is determined or coded by the data contributor.

Label: SpecimenID
Description: Identifying string linked to a particular sample or specimen, provide by the data contributor

Label: TissueVolume
Description: The volume of the tissue sample. Measured in microliters.

Label: FastingState
Description: Was individual fasting when the sample was taken (true/false)

Label: ParentSpecimenType
Description: Type of biological material comprising the Parent Specimen (if applicable)

Label: ReagentLotNumber
Description: The lot number is often provided by a reagent source when the reagent is replenished over time.
Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "reagentLotNumber" is required

Label: TreatmentID(s)
Description: One or more identifiers, separated by a semicolon (;). The treatment identifier(s) must be stored in a data dictionary .csv file uploaded to Synapse
Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "treatmentID(s)" is required

Label: TreatmentTemperatureUnit
Description: Unit of treatment temperature
Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "treatmentTemperatureUnit" is required

Label: SpecifyMeasurementTechnique
Description: Value is determined by the data contributor
Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "specifyMeasurementTechnique" is required

Label: TreatmentAmountValue
Description: The Amount Value indicates how much (concentration, mass, volume) of a treatment agent was applied to a sample.
Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "treatmentAmountValue" is required

Label: TreatmentDurationUnit
Description: Unit of treatment duration
Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "treatmentDurationUnit" is required

Label: TreatmentAmountUnit
Description: Unit of treatment amount
Valid Values: ['iu/l', 'pM', 'DK units/ml', 'pg/nl', 'ng/nl', 'kg', 'mg/dl', 'miu/ml', 'Kallikrein Inactivator Unit per Milliliter', 'AFU', 'Pound', 'ml', 'pg/ml', 'gm', 'TCID50', 'IU', 'ug/ml', 'IU/ml', 'ng/ml', 'NPX', 'mg', 'pg/ul', 'M', 'ug', 'umol/l', 'units/ml', 'AU/ml', 'ng/ul', 'PFU', 'HAU', 'uiu/ml', 'Not Specified', 'ug/ul', 'ng', 'MOI', 'g/l', 'pg', 'PFUe', 'pl', 'mM', 'ul', 'nM', 'mg/l', 'mg/ml', 'ng/dl', 'l', 'g/dl', 'optical density', 'uM', 'nl', 'pg/mg creatinine', 'ug/l', 'ug/dl', 'AI', '']
Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "treatmentAmountUnit" is required

Label: TreatmentName
Description: Treatments refer to in vitro modifications of samples. Three treatment types are supported: agent amount, duration, and temperature.  Treatment name is an alternate identifier to the Treatment ID
Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "treatmentName" is required

Label: TreatmentDurationValue
Description: Duration of treatment
Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "treatmentDurationValue" is required

Label: ReagentWeblink
Description: An internet address that may provide details of an assay reagent.
Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "reagentWeblink" is required

Label: UseTreatment
Description: Was a treatment applied to the sample
Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "useTreatment" is required

Label: TreatmentTemperatureValue
Description: Value of treatment temperature
Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "treatmentTemperatureValue" is required

Label: ReagentName
Description: The reagent name is an alternative to the Reagent ID
Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "reagentName" is required

Label: SpecifySampleType
Description: Value is determined by the data contributor
Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "specifySampleType" is required

Label: ReagentCatalogNumber

Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "reagentCatalogNumber" is required

Label: ReagentContact
Description: The contact information is particularly helpful when the reagent is not from a commercial vendor.
Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "reagentContact" is required

Label: ReagentID(s)
Description: One or more identifiers, separated by a semicolon (;). The reagent identifier(s) must be stored in a data dictionary .csv file uploaded to Synapse
Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "reagentID(s)" is required

Label: UseReagent
Description: Was a reagent applied to the sample
Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "useReagent" is required

Label: Filename
Description: Name of the file. This helps to link annotations from metadata files.
Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "Filename" is required

Label: ReagentManufacturer
Description: The manufacturer is the source of a reagent and may include commercial vendors as well as non-commercial sources (e.g., collaborating labs)
Conditional Requirements: If Assay is "genotyping" then "reagentManufacturer" is required

Label: SpeciesName
Description: The scientific name of the species (typically a taxonomic group, ex. "Eremophila alpestris") the individual belongs to.

Label: Cohort
Description: Name of the cohort the individual belongs to
Valid Values: ['Centenarian', 'US Family', 'Aging', 'and Body Composition Study (HealthABC)', 'Other', 'Denmark Family', 'Unknown', 'The Health', 'Cardiovascular Health Study (CHS)', 'The Osteoporotic Fractures in Men (MrOS) Study', 'Not applicable', 'Study of Osteoporotic Fractures (SOF)', 'Not collected']

Label: Sex
Description: The biological sex of the individual

Label: SpeciesAge
Description: Age of individual (formatted in months, ex. "72 months"). note: Uncertainty about the age might require recording age by specifying a lower and upper estimate in months for the age of the animal.

Label: CaptivityDuration
Description: The duration of captivity in months for the individuals in captivity (formatted in months, ex. 72 months). note: Applicable only to animals with captivity status captive.

Label: LifeStage
Description: The life stage of the individual. note: Other are possible depending on life stage terminology for individual species. Please let the data curation team know.

Label: Taxon
Description: Taxonomic identifier. The National Center for Biotechnology Information taxon ID (formatted as, ex. "txid9989")

Label: SpeciesGroup
Description: The taxonomic ranking including both species and subspecies the individual belongs to.

Label: StudyCode
Description: Unique identifier for the study, assigned by the DCC

Label: CaptivityStatus
Description: The status of the individual with regard to captivity. note: Wild, captive, and stranded values are applicable, especially for marine mammals. Depending on life stage terminology for individual species, other are possible. Please let the data curation team know.

Label: Component
Description: TBD

Description: Identifying string linked to the individual or animal being studied, provided by the data contributor

Label: CommonName
Description: The biological species common name the individual belongs to (ex. "Horned Lark").note: As a default, the valid scientific name for the species should be indicated.

Description: Sample batch lot identifier, provided by the data contributor to Sage Bionetworks. The batch identifier(s) must be stored in a data dictionary .csv file uploaded to Synapse

Label: LibraryBatchID
Description: Library batch identifier, provided by the data contributor to Sage Bionetworks. The batch identifier(s) must be stored in a data dictionary .csv file uploaded to Synapse

Label: TotalReads
Description: Total number of sequencing reads from a library.

Label: ReadStrandOrigin
Description: The strand from which the read originates in a strand-specific protocol

Label: ResultUnit
Description: The unit for the result value

Label: SpecifyRNABatchSizeUnit
Description: Value is determined by the data contributor

Label: SpecimenID
Description: Identifying string linked to a particular sample or specimen, provide by the data contributor

Label: RunType
Description: The type of run

Label: Filename
Description: Name of the file. This helps to link annotations from metadata files.
